or marine life. A proactive approach to obtain a biopsy for histopathological 
and microbiological diagnosis is advised. Anti-mycobacterial treatment should be 
started promptly. The combined use of rifampicin, ethambutol, and clarithromycin 
appears to be effective, and debridement is indicated in patients with 
deep-seated infections.

