As life expectancy of patients infected by Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV) 
has prolonged, they are treated by physicians of different specialities. This 
article focuses on urologic complications of HIV infection. Urinary tract 
infections in HIV positive patients are more frequent than in otherwise healthy 
